Loved ones of a missing UCT student are frantically searching for her. 19-year-old, Uyinene Mrwetyana, was last seen at the weekend. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Loved ones of a missing UCT student are frantically searching for her. Uyinene Mrwetyana (19) was last seen at the weekend. South Africans have been rallying on social media, hoping for her safe return. According to the police, Mrwetyana was last seen on Saturday afternoon in the Claremont area on her way to the Post Office. READ: Search continues for missing UCT student DispatchLIVE reported that two more investigators have been hired to assist the police and private investigator Noel Pratten in their search. Her worried friends have been holding prayer meetings and are hopeful that she'll return home unharmed.